    return li

    def bubble_sort(li):
    n = len(li)
    for i in range(n):      # 0ë¶€í„° n-1ê¹Œì§€
        for j in range(0,n-i):# jëŠ” í•­ìƒ 0ë¶€í„°ì´ë˜, n-iê¹Œì§€ë§Œë°˜ë³µ
            if j==(n-1):      # indexError ë°©ì§€.
                pass
            elif li[j] > li[j+1]:
                li[j], li[j+1] = li[j+1], li[j]     # êµí™˜
            else :
                pass
    return li

    def quick_sort(li):
    if len(li)<=1:
        return li
    else:
        L1, L2 = [], []
        for x in li[1:]:
            if x<=li[0]:
                L1.append(x)
            else :
                L2.append(x)
        return quick_sort( L1 ) + quick_sort([ li[0] ]) + quick_sort( L2 )
